narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you have taken Spanish before, don't purposely do badly on the placement test.It makes it tough for students who are new to the language.
much harder than spanish 1 but still very manageable
If you have to take it, then yes. I would recommend OScar.

Spanish 120 is a continuation of learning from Spanish 110; however, it is more difficult and has more work. You have to spend some time really working on the things that are assigned to you for you to be able to understand them completely. I would recommend this class to people who are interested in Spanish.

Learning basic grammar and vocabulary. I would recommend it if you want to have a good foundation in the language. It's not hard as long as you put some effort into it, and the teachers are very eager to help students succeed.

I would recommend this class for anyone who needs to fill a language requirement or wishes to actually learn the Spanish language. It is more in depth than Spanish I with more intense conjugations and vocabulary.
